Executive Profile
Christopher P. Mottern  Chief Executive Officer, Free-Flow Packaging International, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships73--
Background

		Mr. Christopher P. Mottern, also known as Chris, has been Chief Executive Officer of Free-Flow Packaging International, Inc., since March 2012. Mr. Mottern served as the Chairman of the Board of Peet's Coffee & Tea Inc. since May 2002 and as its Chief Executive Officer and President from May 1997 to May 2002. Mr. Mottern was responsible for significantly expanding Peet's' presence outside the Bay Area and for taking it public. Prior to Peet's, Mr. Mottern served as President ... of The Heublein Wines Group from July 1992 to September 1996. From 1986 through 1991, he served as President and Chief Executive Officer of Capri Sun, Inc. He has been an Independent Director of Farmer Brothers Co. since December 5, 2013. Mr. Mottern has been a Director of Coen, Inc. since 1990. He serves as a Director of TBC Worldwide, Inc. He served as a Director of Peet's Coffee & Tea Inc. from August 1997 to December 31, 2004. He served as a Director of Valley Media Inc. since March 1997. He is a graduate of the University of Connecticut.Read Full Background




